                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-26T13:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. The President and I are officially informed that the loan contract has been
                    signed in New York between Keilhauer representing the Government of Salvador and
                    Mr. Keith.<note n="7" xml:id="d786fn7">The Minister had advised the Department,
                        June 22, that Salvador had authorized Mr. René Keilhauer to sign modified
                        loan contract with Mr. Minor C. Keith, and that the latter would himself
                        make the loan (file no. 816.51/168). The contract was signed on June 24
                        (file no. 816.51/182).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
